raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "perl-moose" %}
{% set version = "2.2207" %}
{% set sha256 = "7c2daddc49754ded93f65b8ce9e3ac9b6d11ab27d111ec77f95a8528cf4ac409" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://cpan.metacpan.org/authors/id/E/ET/ETHER/Moose-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}
  patches:
    - cross-compile.patch       # [target_platform != build_platform]

build:
  skip: true  # [win]
  number: 2
  run_exports:
    weak:
      - {{ name }} ={{ version }}

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - {{ stdlib('c') }}
    - make  # [not win]
    #- m2-make  # [win]
  host:
    - perl
    - perl-cpan-meta-check
    - perl-module-runtime
    - perl-devel-globaldestruction
    - perl-package-stash
    - perl-class-load-xs
    - perl-devel-overloadinfo
    - perl-devel-stacktrace
    - perl-params-util
    - perl-try-tiny
    - perl-module-runtime-conflicts
    - perl-package-deprecationmanager
    - perl-class-load
    - perl-dist-checkconflicts
    - perl-mro-compat
    - perl-eval-closure
    - perl-sub-exporter
    - perl-package-stash-xs
    - perl-data-optlist
    - perl-test-fatal
    - perl-test-needs
    - perl-test-requires
    - perl-test-cleannamespaces
    - perl-scalar-list-utils # for List::Util. It's in core, but too old.
  run:
    - perl

test:
  imports:
    - Moose
    - Moose::Deprecated
    - Moose::Exception
